body:
Australia Test captain Pat Cummins will take an eight-week hiatus to recharge as he prepares for the highly anticipated Border-Gavaskar Trophy series against India later this year. Fresh off his debut stint in Major League Cricket in the United States, Cummins has opted for rest and recuperation, stepping away from next month's white-ball tour of the United Kingdom.

